replies.msg: My friend Charles is a Gemini while his girlfriend is a Virgo. He's faithful to her and would never cheat on her. When he broke up with his ex he was driven over the edge. Even when a stranger talked to him there was an edge of hostility to his voice. But as soon as he had a new relationship target it took the edge of his emotional upset. His ex is a swimming champion who easily outshines us in any swimming styles. Shes tall and shapely who definitely has the edge over lots of swimmers. Recently he got into a brawl with a guy who was hitting on his girlfriend. The police showed up later and assigned jealousy as the motive for the brawl. Just the other day they dined in a restaurant of a hotel which is midway between the supermarket and his place. They queued for almost an hour outside the restaurant. The queue was so huge that it stretched from the counter through the lobby area and out the main entrance to the hotel. A stout guy tried to cut in line but was caught. Yesterday I visited his place. We met at a midway point between his place and mine then he took me to the bus bound for his home. A group of guys were in the way near the bus stop so he said "excuse me" The line was so big stretching down the road to the furthest mini bus stop. We stood in line for half an hour until three shuttle buses came along. Meanwhile some people mistook this big queue for the queue for other places. A couple came up and asked "are you in the queue for Cluny park?" as they wanna be sure that it's the right place. A stout man pushed in. Later a slim guy jumped the queue. The lady behind him said "excuse me. The end of the queue is back there" A woman stood beside a guy who was midway through the queue. While preyendikh to look at her phone she edged furtively behind him who didn't realise she was there. Some people might have noticed it but ignored it. Charles seemed on edge. It turns out that he as a job interview tomorrow. Never has he felt so on edge before an interview. I said "I'm rooting for you" My brother too said "I support you. It's going to be ok. I'm there for you." My girlfriend also said "I've got your back." His girlfriend has  geography exam at university soon so shes busy with revision. I said "you're almost there." My brother too said "you got this. I believe in you." When her professor was tutoring her in geography he said "now you've got the hang of it. You're on the right track now. Keep it up!" Jason's elder brother is currently a head chef at a five star hotel and feels hea found his niche. His younger brother has also found his niche as a professor having worked as a researcher for three years. He sometimes has a snooze during lunchtime as he has so much work to do that he feels drained. He usually naps on the sofa or at his desk by the fireplace when everybody else's eating lunch outside. He once brought his work along to the library where he dozed off at the table. Having a doze especially by the fire is a marvellous way to replenish your energy though. His eldest brother has just completed his phd at tokyo university and is on the way to becoming a professor. Japan is on the way to becoming the worlds strongest economy. His elder sister is robust and healthy. She does lots of strength and conditioning exercises in her robust sneakers. After her gym session she usually drinks a glass of robust wine and a cup of robust coffee. She luves in korea where the political system and economy are robust. His younger sister has opened an antique shop which made a great impression on me. There's an exquisite antique which engages my interest. I'll bet the shop engages many passers-by. I had a favorable impression of it. His uncle has recently passed away at the age of ninety nine. I offer my sincere condolences to his uncle's family. His friend ken said "My condolences on the loss of your uncle" His dad too sent his condolences to his uncle's family. Hos mum wrote "our condolences go to his family."

My friend Jason is also a gemini while his girlfriend is a Scorpio. He hadn't  heard from his cousin for years until yesterday when he received a call from her. They chatted in exquisite delight. She told him that there was a bully in her class at university so Jason told her not to engage with her. Just stay out of her way as much as possible. Jason lives in the most exclusive and expensive area in central and owns many houses. Unlike Mayweather he's never ostentatious though extremely wealthy. You can find out how ostentatious Mayweather's lifestyle is such as his house and car collections. He always wears ostentatious jewelry such as gold necklaces, rings and silver bracelets. He loves driving flashy cars and wearing flashy clothes. Do you remember the incident in Langham place where the escalator stopped and reversed direction at a speed two to three times faster than normal causing people to fall and pile up at the base of the escalator? People were screaming as they tumbled down the escalator. Some people managed to grab the handrail and steady themselves. The incident occasioned a good deal of worry. When you were at secondary school were there any subjects which you weren't interested in and so didn't engage much in the classes? I remember I didn't really engage in geography classes. I was often daydreaming. Today many students learn piano, violin, japanese, dancing, judo and painting. I honestly don't know how they juggle these activities and schoolwork. Some of their parents have to go to work every day and so find it hard to juggle children with a career. Perhaps they wanna kindle their kids' interest and see which one they can cultivate an interest in or have a talent for. Sometimes I wonder if the children are truly enjoying their activitues. Jason loves video games. I remember him play Counterstrike in which he used a gun to single-handedly engage ninety nine enemies who only had knives lol. I'm reading a book called parallel worlds written by physicist Kaku. When he was explaining the theories promoting the book on a television show it captured my imagination. It's a fascinating book that explores the science of time travel, parallel universes, wormholes and eleven dimensional hyperspace, subjects that engage numerous readers' attention. I find the subject of wormholes most engaging. It was an international bestseller for many months. Jason is a bunny lover. He has a Holland lop and a Netherland dwarf. In accordance with animal law in Kyoto if your pet is a social animal you must have at least two of them living together. Most citizens honour it. According to the veterinarians you should clip your bunny's nails every month. Rabbits are compatible with most other pets if you teach the other pets well. At tokyo university researchers carried out an experiment last year and this afternoon where they showed they could bond a rabbit with a dog over a short period of time. They were happy to find their results were compatible with the results of the study that was undertaken last year. Hereafter Jason had his Shiba Inu and his bunnies living together. He believes that he'll continue living with them in the hereafter. You can take the house rabbit journals for free and read them at your leisure.
